The paper deals with named-entity recognition (NER) using artificial neural networks (ANNs), which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses transfer learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), and can be applied to various tasks. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with patient note de-identification, which is a specific application of NER in the healthcare domain. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category.
